Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.54,0:00:10.33,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon pages and pages of entries
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:14.47,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,We've put down all our emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.97,0:00:17.76,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,But now I've hit a writer's block
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.01,0:00:21.73,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to finish this page anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.98,0:00:24.92,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Putting a bookmark in my diary
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.54,0:00:29.96,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I go out to ride the bike we found in the dumpster
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.36,0:00:33.12,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to our secret place
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:37.46,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Where we piled up our bricks of memories
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.26,0:00:42.72,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Run up the hill, where we can see the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.75,0:00:47.26,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Where we can see the sky so fearfully blue
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:50.48,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,With cider in my right hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.48,0:00:54.99,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,My other hand helps me search for you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.72,0:00:59.11,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You used to come find me way back when
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:02.80,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You used to demand me of so much more
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.80,0:01:09.58,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You're both still standing right by my side
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.91,0:01:17.36,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet why do I pray to see you both again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.56,0:01:25.47,Opening 2,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be something off with me
